    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-10-19T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-10-19T12:00:00-05:00" n="73"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/4263: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hawks</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-19T11:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>118. Honduran Minister informs me that General Jeffries is aiding Honduran <hi
                        rend="italic">emigrados</hi> in revolutionary activities. He requests that
                    Jeffries be deported to the United States or at least concentrated here under
                    police surveillance. Please instruct immediately whether I should make such
                    request of the Government of Guatemala. I recommend that one of the two courses
                    be taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hawks</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
